{"title_page": "From Nurse to Worse (Saved by the Bell)", "text_new": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:From Nurse to Worse (''Saved by the Bell'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title = From Nurse to Worse\n| image =\n| caption = \n| series = [[Saved by the Bell]]\n| season = 2\n| episode = 16\n| production = 6333\n| airdate = {{Start date|1990|12|15}}\n| writer = Bennett Tramer\n| director = Don Barnhart \n| photographer = \n| music = Scott Gale\n| guests = *Pamela Kosh as Miss Simpson\n*[[Nancy Valen]] as Jennifer\n*Justine Lenore as Nurse Butcher (uncredited)\n*Mark Neal as Kyle Kapowski (uncredited) (voice)\n| prev = The Fabulous Belding Boys\n| next = Breaking Up is Hard to Undo\n| episode_list = List of Saved by the Bell episodes\n| season_article = Saved by the Bell (season 1)\n}}\n\n'''\"From Nurse to Worse\"''' is the sixteenth episode<ref>{{cite web |url=https://homeless-wino.livejournal.com/5136.html|title=Episodes sixteen and nineteen|last= |first= |date=December 9, 2009|website=Saved By the Bell: An analysis|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/11/every-episode-of-saved-by-the-bell-ranked.html|title=Every Episode of Saved by the Bell, Ranked From Worst to Best|last=Fitzmaurice|first=Larry|date=November 2, 2015|website=Vulture|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://podcast.app/from-nurse-to-worse-e25497919/|title=31 From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date=November 21, 2017|website=Saved by the Bell with Millennials|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> of the second season<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/7492/saved-by-the-bell-seasons-1-2/|title=Saved by the Bell - Seasons 1 & 2|last= |first= |date=September 2, 2003|website=DVD Talk|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> of the American [[teen sitcom]] ''[[Saved by the Bell]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/photos/saved-bell-turns-25-back-shows-best-fashions-25022797/image-25023063|title='Saved By the Bell' Turns 25: Look Back on the Show's Best Fashions|last= |first= |date= |website=ABC News|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> originally airing on December 15, 1990 on [[NBC]]. The episode was written by Bennett Tramer<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thesummerofmorris.blogspot.com/2010/07/from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=From Nurse to Worse|last=Morris|first=Derek|date=July 29, 2010|website=The Summer of Morris|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> and was directed by Don Barnhart<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gIpykjBvy/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>.\n\nIn this episode, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Zack Morris|Zack]] ([[Mark-Paul Gosselaar]]) asks [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Kelly Kapowski|Kelly]] ([[Tiffani Thiessen]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090924191747/http://www.thiessenpictures.com/index.php?cat=17|title=SEASONS 1 + 2 SCREENCAPS|last= |first= |date=December 17, 2006 |website=Tiffani Thiessen Photo Gallery|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>) to [[Courtship|go steady]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcswithrsp.blogspot.com/2011/03/classic-sbtb-from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=Classic SBTB: From Nurse To Worse|last= |first= |date=March 14, 2011|website=ABCs wth RSP|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kktybayside.blogspot.com/2011/01/from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=From Nurse to Worse|last=Weber|first=Korey|date=January 20, 2011|website=KKTY Bayside|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> with him, but while she is thinking it over, he falls<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sbtbreviewed.com/post/104670308015/sbtb-reviewed-episode-35-from-nurse-to-worse|title=SbtB Reviewed Episode 35: From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date= December 8, 2014|website=SbtB Reviewed|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> for a (supposedly) new student ([[Nancy Valen]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://podcasts.apple.com/au/podcast/nancy-valen-baywatch-heavenly-kid-nurse-jennifer-on/id1243077571?i=1000438680491|title=Nancy Valen (Baywatch, The Heavenly Kid, and \"Nurse Jennifer\" on Saved by the Bell)|last= |first= |date=May 17, 2019|website=Reliving My Youth|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://starsandcelebs.com/2010/09/eleven-people-might-not-know-saved-bell/|title=Eleven people you might not know were on 'Saved by the Bell'|last= |first= |date=September 27, 2010|website=Stars and Celebs|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://luminarypodcasts.com/listen/music-mania-286/saved-by-nostalgia-podcast/sbtb-from-nurse-to-worse-s2-e13/021d54f4-edbb-45a3-935a-4f2b4d78f7d1?country=US|title=SBTB- From Nurse to Worse (S2 E13)|last= |first= |date=July 5, 2019|website=SAVED BY NOSTALGIA PODCAST|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>), only to discover that she is actually the new school nurse.<ref>{{YouTube|title=45 - Saved By The Bell - S3E16 - From Nurse to Worse|id=lH96JoWcuMM}}</ref> Meanwhile, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#A.C. Slater|Slater]] ([[Mario Lopez]]) is afraid of getting his [[Influenza vaccine|flu shot]].\n\n==Plot==\nZack and Kelly arrive back at Kelly's house<ref>{{cite web |url=http://netchic.tripod.com/fromnursetoworse.html|title=SBTB - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date= |website=netchic.tripod.com|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> after their date to the movie ''[[Ernest Goes to Jail]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://savedbythebellblog.wordpress.com/2014/01/08/nurse-wretched/|title=Nurse Wretched|last= |first= |date=January 8, 2014|website=The Saved by the Bell Blog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> While at the front porch<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-k7DgJD5ey/|title=sbtbanniversary WEDNESDAY, APRIL 4, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 4, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>, Zack first ask Kelly that he wants to go steady with her before being interrupted by the voice Kelly's meddling little brother Kyle (Mark Neal) from upstairs. Kelly tells Zack that going steady is a big decision that she has to sleep on. The next day at Bayside, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Samuel \"Screech\" Powers|Screech]] ([[Dustin Diamond]]), [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Lisa Turtle|Lisa]], Jessie and Slater are discussing the upcoming school physical with Nurse Butcher (Justine Lenore<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epicsavedbythebell.blogspot.com/2014/02/sbtb-0216-from-nurse-to-worse.html |title=SBTB 02.16. - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first=|date=February 21, 2014|website=Epic Saved by the Bell|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gKLTsjkUz/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>). While Screech prepares by [[Exercise|exercising]] in the hallway, Jessie ([[Elizabeth Berkley]]) is emphatic that she's already in perfect health. Slater, meanwhile confesses that he doesn't like the annual physical, but won't further elaborate. Zack soon walks in and tells the gang about his intent on asking Kelly to go steady with him. The news is so hot, that Lisa ([[Lark Voorhies]]) plans to [[Gossip|spread it]] all around school.\n\nAs students clear out upon the ringing of the [[school bell]], Zack approached by a beautiful<ref>{{cite web |url=https://goat.com.au/saved-by-the-bell/30-years-on-zack-morris-is-still-the-most-problematic-character-in-saved-by-the-bell/|title=30 Years On, Zack Morris Is Still The Most Problematic Character In Saved By The Bell|last=Pan|first=Alexander|date=August 21, 2019|website=Goat|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> young woman named Jennifer<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/omarvillegas/a-definitive-ranking-of-guest-characters-on-saved-by-the-bel|title=A Definitive Ranking Of Guest Characters On \"Saved By The Bell\"|last=Villegas|first=Omar|date=October 17, 2014|website=Buzzfeed|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ([[Nancy Valen]]) who asks him for directions to the nurse's office. Zack is suddenly so [[Love at first sight|enamored]] by being in the woman's presence, that he is left literally [[Aphasia|speechless]]. Next in [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Mrs. Simpson|Miss Simpson's]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://the-talk.freeforums.net/thread/5538/saved-bell-episode-reviews-thread?page=27|title=SBTB 02.16. - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date=December 29, 2014|website=Saved By The Bell Episode Reviews Thread|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> (Pamela Kosh<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gKh68jHQ9/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>) classroom, she informs her students about the [[Poetry|poems]] that they were supposed to write for [[English studies|English]] class. Right after Screech and Lisa read their respective poems, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Mr. Belding|Mr. Belding]] ([[Dennis Haskins]]) addresses the students on the [[intercom]] to remind them of the annual [[Physical examination|physicals]] and flu shots. When Belding himself volunteers for a shot<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-qWd17DHVb/|title=sbtbanniversary FRIDAY, APRIL 6, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 6, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>, he is overheard shrieking in pain, much to the discomfort of Slater. Finally when it's Kelly's turn to read her romantically themed poem, Zack imagines his new found [[Infatuation|crush]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://jumpedthesnark.com/2011/02/21/gratuitous-search-term-bait-of-the-day-hello-nurse/|title=Gratuitous Search Term Bait of the Day: Hellooooo Nurse|last= |first= |date=February 21, 2011|website=Jumped The Shark|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Jennifer addressing it towards him. Soon, Mr. Belding comes back on the intercom to tell Jessie and Zack to report to the nurse's office<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-k6-9eDRWq/|title=sbtbanniversary WEDNESDAY, APRIL 4, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 4, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>.\n\nWhile taking an [[eye examination]], Nurse Butcher tells Jessie that she's afraid that she might need glasses. After Butcher and Jessie leave, Jennifer walks in, now wearing her white [[White coat|medical coat]] and [[nurse uniform]]. To Zack's surprise, Jennifer tells him that she will be taking over from Nurse Butcher full-time the following month. Meanwhile, Kelly and Screech are in the hallway waiting for the end of Zack's physical. Kelly soon lets Screech in on her intent on saying yes<ref>{{cite web |url=https://guff.com/moments-that-prove-saved-by-the-bells-zack-morris-was-a-homicidal-maniac|title=Moments That Prove Saved by the Bell's Zack Morris Was a Homicidal Maniac|last=Porter |first=Joseph|date= |website=Guff|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to going steady with Zack. But as soon as Kelly sees Zack return from the nurse's office, he is completely oblivious to Kelly's feelings at the moment. Meanwhile, at The Max, Slater is trying to persuade Lisa or Jessie to [[Signature forgery|forge]] his mother's signature to get out of having to take the required flu shot at Bayside. Afterwards, an upset Kelly walks in and addresses to Lisa and Jessie her concerns about Zack not wanting to go out with her anymore. Jessie tries to calm Kelly's fears by telling her that she'll personally talk to Zack about the matter.\n\nIn Zack's bedroom, he is practicing [[flirting]] with Jennifer while in front of a mirror and wearing a [[Suit|suit]] and [[Necktie|tie]]. Soon, Jessie arrives via the open window and begins to inquire Zack about whether or not he's backing out on asking Kelly to go steady with him. Zack immediately confesses to Jessie about being in love<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/11/ranking-saved-by-the-bells-zack-morris-love-interests/|title=Ranking Saved By The Bell\u2019s Zack Morris\u2019 Love Interests|last=Fee|first=Rob |date=November 13, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> with Jennifer, the new school nurse.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thefederalist.com/2014/09/12/yo-slate-get-saved-by-the-bell-right/|title=Yo, Slate, Get \u2018Saved By The Bell\u2019 Right|last=Payne|first=Daniel|date=September 12, 2014|website=The Federalist|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> When a disgusted Jessie asks Zack if he somehow plans on dating Kelly and Jennifer at the same time, Zack begins to [[Sexual fantasy|fantasize]] about being a surgeon with Jennifer and Kelly<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-ngDqjjQ_v/|title=sbtbanniversary THURSDAY, APRIL 5, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 5, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/from-nurse-to-worse-episode-16-air-date-pictured-nancy-news-photo/141349256|title=SAVED BY THE BELL -- \"From Nurse to Worse\" Episode 16 -- Air Date 12/15/1990 -- Pictured: (l-r) Nancy Valen as Jennifer, Mark-Paul Gosselaar as Zack Morris, Tiffani Thiessen as Kelly Kapowski -- Photo by: Gary Null/NBCU Photo Bank|last= |first= |date= |website=Getty Images|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> as his nursing assistants. Although Jessie notes to Zack about how upset Kelly is going to be, Zack reminds Jessie that she promised not to tell anybody. While back in Miss Simpson's classroom, Zack feigns illness as a means of going back to the nurse's office to see Jennifer. Mr. Belding then walks in to tell Slater to report to his physical. In the nurse's office, Zack tells Jennifer that his head is [[Fever|feeling hot]] despite it feeling cool when Jennifer touches it. Shortly after Jennifer leaves the room to get her [[Medical thermometer|thermometer]] to take Zack's temperature, Slater walks in for his dreaded flu shot. But with the curtain drawn forward, Zack mistakenly believes that Slater is Jennifer. It is there that Zack inadvertently confesses to Slater his true feelings about Jennifer. Slater proceeds to [[blackmail]] Zack into another flu shot so that he won't tell Kelly or anybody else about his feelings for Jennifer.\n\nAt The Max, Zack desperately asks Screech if he knows anybody who could take Kelly's mind off him for a while so that he can pursue<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/10/the-30-greatest-episodes-of-saved-by-the-bell/|title=The 30 Greatest Episodes Of Saved By The Bell|last=Fee|first=Rob|date=October 28, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Jennifer. Screech then tells Zack about a new kid at school named Melvin Nerdly, who is a substitute on is [[Chess club|chess team]]. Shortly thereafter, Kelly walks in and is told by Zack that they should date other people for the time being. When Jessie, Slater and Lisa see Kelly suddenly leave in a huff, Lisa wonders what is troubling Kelly. Lisa though is immediately able to decipher Jessie and Slater's [[Cant (language)#Argot|secret language]] regarding the promise that they made to Zack about not telling anybody about his infatuation with Jennifer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.funnyordie.com/zack-morris-is-trash/2018/10/12/17965460/zack-morris-is-trash-dumped-girlfriend-school-nurse-saved-by-the-bell|title=The Time Zack Morris Dumped His Girlfriend To Harass The School Nurse|last=Driscoll|first=Dashiell|date=October 12, 2018|website=Funny or Die|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> So Lisa then, leads the way in telling Jennifer about Zack's neglect of Kelly. Jennifer when informed of this tells Jessie, Slater and Lisa to leave everything to her as she has had plenty of experience dealing with \"sick people\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldation.com/stories/ever-happened-women-saved-bell/|title=What ever happened to the women of Saved by the Bell?|last=Levis|first=Jamie|date=February 16, 2020|website=Worldnation|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Meanwhile, Jessie is emphatic that she didn't fail her initial eye exam under Nurse Butcher. Jennifer tells Jessie that the reason why she's retiring is due to her own failing [[Visual perception|eyesight]] and thus, Jessie doesn't need glasses after-all.\n\nThe next day, Zack enters the nurse's office upon Jennifer's request. When Zack sees Jennifer, she dressed decidedly more provocatively than her usual white nurse uniform: A purple [[T-shirt]], black [[miniskirt|tube miniskirt]], [[pantyhose]], a black [[Western wear|western]] [[Belt (clothing)|waist belt]], [[Shoulder pads (fashion)|shoulder pads]], [[Earring#Hoop earrings|hoop earrings]] and [[Court shoe|black pumps]]. Shortly thereafter, Jennifer locks the door, and while complaining about the warmth in the room, [[Seduction|sensually]] takes off her white coat, and takes out the [[Hair stick|stick]] that was holding her hair in a [[Bun (hairstyle)|bun]].<ref>{{YouTube|title=Nancy Valen lets her hair down. American actress takes stick out of her hair to drop bun. Beautiful|id=1BbRBsOCsjY}}</ref> Zack then nervously listens while Jennifer tells him about how she can't stop thinking about him<ref>{{cite web |url=https://postgradproblems.com/power-ranking-every-saved-by-the-bell-character/|title=Power Ranking Every \"Saved By The Bell\" Character|last= |first=|date=November 2, 2015 |website=Post Grad Problems|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> and how he's sweet unlike her fictional husband. Zack proceeds to panic when Jennifer tells him that her \"husband\" is a [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]] with a violent [[Temperament|temper]]. When Zack attempts to leave, Jennifer immediately corners him and tells him about how they should not only run away together, but also get married and have lots of children. Zack then tries to tell Jennifer that he already has a girlfriend in Kelly and that one girl is all that he can handle. Before finally allowing him to leave, Jennifer grabs Zack by the collar and boldly asks him if he wants a girl or a woman<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-qd-7-jUC3/|title=sbtbanniversary FRIDAY, APRIL 6, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 6, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>.\n\nThat evening, Zack is back at Kelly's front porch, where he finds finds Kelly on a date with Melvin Nerdly. Not only does Melvin play [[Chess|chess]], but [[List of multi-sport athletes|also]] [[American football|football]] and [[Ice hockey|hockey]] while also [[Model (person)|modeling]] a little. Zack tries to tell<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kiwireport.com/cast-saved-bell-now/|title=The cast of Saved by the Bell: then & now|last=Stevens|first=Stephanie|date=April 23, 2017|website=Kiwi Report|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Kelly that he really does want to go out with her and nobody else only to be immediately shut down by her. As Zack pleads to Kelly to take him back, Kyle upstairs warns Zack that he should leave or he'll be sorry. When Zack tells Kyle to mind his own business, Kyle retaliates by dumping a bucket a water on top of Zack's head.\n\n==Production==\nBefore Nancy Valen<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-imU58jPjv/|title=sbtbanniversary TUESDAY, APRIL 3, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 3, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=Splat From The Past #16- Nancy Valen|id=xBsQaSofv8M}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://open.spotify.com/episode/5myq4jJssbuUjPVI5e5Wym?si=YUDHMCalRMWbNlSc4hLn6A|title=TV Guidance Counselor Episode 382: Nancy Valen|last=Reid |first=Ken|date= |website=TV Guidance Counselor Podcast|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> was cast as Nurse Jennifer,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ebaumsworld.com/pictures/13-things-you-didnt-know-about-saved-by-the-bell/84305926/|title=13 Things You Didn't Know About Saved By The Bell|last= |first= |date=September 30, 2014|website=eBaum's World|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> supermodel [[Kathy Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-ilUUmDdut/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 3, 2020 |website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gJQPtDlXF/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> was going to play<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tvovermind.com/10-things-didnt-know-saved-by-the-bell/|title=10 Things You Didn\u2019t Know About \u2018Saved by the Bell\u2019|last=Gerstenberger|first=Tim|date= |website=TV Overmind|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> the part. Ireland was however ultimately fired<ref>{{cite book |last=Ireland|first=Kathy|author-link= |date= |title=Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons That Will Change Your Life|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sphMwR7I6dwC&pg=PT70&lpg=PT70&dq=kathy+ireland+nurse+saved+by+the+bell&source=bl&ots=6H-MLLQBvK&sig=ACfU3U0-CcBF4NRfjTltKnMqkdPh3f8neQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjGprnZhdHoAhUGeKwKHXsFBhEQ6AEwFHoECA8QKQ#v=onepage&q=kathy%20ireland%20nurse%20saved%20by%20the%20bell&f=false|location= |publisher= |page= |isbn=}}</ref> during rehearsals after a disappointing [[Read-through|table read]] and a similarly disappointing [[Rehearsal#Dress rehearsal|dress rehearsal]]. \u201cShe must have dazzled us in the office, because I hired her on the spot,\u201d recalled co-creator [[Peter Engel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blog.truffleshuffle.co.uk/2015/01/10-things-you-probably-didnt-know-about%E2%80%A6saved-by-the-bell/|title=10 Things You [Probably] Didn\u2019t Know About\u2026Saved by the Bell|last= |first= |date=January 17, 2015|website=Truffle Shuffle|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Engel soon called Ireland's manager<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/10-things-you-didnt-know-about-saved-by-the-bell|title=10 Things You Didn't Know About 'Saved by the Bell'|last= |first= |date=August 20, 2014|website=Fox News|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to inform him that she couldn't do the part.\n\nKathy Ireland would right in her book ''Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons That Will Change Your Life'' that upon reading the script, she thought that her part was a little silly and she really couldn't connect with her character. Ireland added that she started asking herself a lot of questions, which resulted in her losing her focus. When the director kept telling her to just read her lines and to flirt with the boy (Zack) in a fantasy scene, Ireland attested that she didn't feel comfortable coming on<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angelfire.com/80s/superstar10/sbtb.html|title=Inconsistencies on Saved by the Bell|last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to a teenager. Ireland proclaimed that she just wasn't good enough of an actress to be able to give the director something that would make him happy without compromising her beliefs.\n\nMeanwhile, Jennifer calls Zack \"Loverboy\" when she tells Jessie, Slater and Lisa about getting him in her nurse's office and letting him see a side of her that he has never seen before. One year prior, Nancy Valen appeared in the 1989 film ''[[Loverboy (1989 film)|Loverboy]]'' also as a woman named [[Jennifer (given name)|Jennifer]] (or Jenny in this case).\n\n==Reception==\nLarry Fitzmaurice of [[Vulture.com]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/11/every-episode-of-saved-by-the-bell-ranked.html|title=Every Episode of Saved by the Bell, Ranked From Worst to Best|last=Fitzmaurice|first=Larry|date=November 2, 2015|website=Vulture|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ranked \"From Nurse to Worse\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225061544/http://www.savedbythebellreviewed.com/2014/08/22/saved-by-the-bell-season-2-episode-16-from-nurse-to-worse/|title=Saved by the Bell Season 2, Episode 16: \"From Nurse to Worse\"|last= |first= |date=August 22, 2014|website=Saved by the Bell...Reviewed!|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> at #74 among the 81 episodes (discounting its prequel, ''[[Good Morning, Miss Bliss]]'', [[Clip show|clip-show]] episodes, and combining two-part episodes into one) produced. Meanwhile, Rob Fee of ''[[Thought Catalog]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/10/the-30-greatest-episodes-of-saved-by-the-bell/ |title=The 30 Greatest Episodes Of Saved By The Bell|last=Fee|first=Rob|date=October 28, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ranked \"From Nurse to Worse\" at #30 among the top 30 greatest ''Saved by the Bell'' episodes. [[Uproxx]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uproxx.com/tv/all-86-saved-by-the-bell-episodes-definitively-ranked-by-imdb-users/|title=All 86 \u2018Saved By The Bell\u2019 Episodes, Definitively Ranked! (By IMDb Users)|last=Cormier|first=Roger|date=August 18, 2014|website=Uproxx|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> complied a ranking of episodes by [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]] users and \"From Nurse to Worse\" received a score of 7.1 from 57 users (10), thus coming in #25 out of 86 episodes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb episode|0695194|From Nurse to Worse}}\n* {{tv.com episode|from-nurse-to-worse-21737|From Nurse to Worse}}\n\n{{Saved by the Bell}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:From Nurse to Worse (Saved by the Bell)}}\n[[Category:1990 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Fictional nurses]]\n[[Category:Saved by the Bell (season 2) episodes]]\n", "text_old": "{{DISPLAYTITLE:From Nurse to Worse (''Saved by the Bell'')}}\n{{Infobox television episode\n| title = From Nurse to Worse\n| image =\n| caption = \n| series = [[Saved by the Bell]]\n| season = 2\n| episode = 16\n| production = 6333\n| airdate = {{Start date|1990|12|15}}\n| writer = Bennett Tramer\n| director = Don Barnhart \n| photographer = \n| music = Scott Gale\n| guests = *Pamela Kosh as Miss Simpson\n*[[Nancy Valen]] as Jennifer\n*Justine Lenore as Nurse Butcher (uncredited)\n*Mark Neal as Kyle Kapowski (uncredited) (voice)\n| prev = The Fabulous Belding Boys\n| next = Breaking Up is Hard to Undo\n| episode_list = List of Saved by the Bell episodes\n| season_article = Saved by the Bell (season 1)\n}}\n\n'''\"From Nurse to Worse\"''' is the sixteenth episode<ref>{{cite web |url=https://homeless-wino.livejournal.com/5136.html|title=Episodes sixteen and nineteen|last= |first= |date=December 9, 2009|website=Saved By the Bell: An analysis|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/11/every-episode-of-saved-by-the-bell-ranked.html|title=Every Episode of Saved by the Bell, Ranked From Worst to Best|last=Fitzmaurice|first=Larry|date=November 2, 2015|website=Vulture|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://podcast.app/from-nurse-to-worse-e25497919/|title=31 From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date=November 21, 2017|website=Saved by the Bell with Millennials|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> of the second season<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dvdtalk.com/reviews/7492/saved-by-the-bell-seasons-1-2/|title=Saved by the Bell - Seasons 1 & 2|last= |first= |date=September 2, 2003|website=DVD Talk|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> of the American [[teen sitcom]] ''[[Saved by the Bell]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/photos/saved-bell-turns-25-back-shows-best-fashions-25022797/image-25023063|title='Saved By the Bell' Turns 25: Look Back on the Show's Best Fashions|last= |first= |date= |website=ABC News|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> originally airing on December 15, 1990 on [[NBC]]. The episode was written by Bennett Tramer<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thesummerofmorris.blogspot.com/2010/07/from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=From Nurse to Worse|last=Morris|first=Derek|date=July 29, 2010|website=The Summer of Morris|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> and was directed by Don Barnhart<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gIpykjBvy/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>.\n\nIn this episode, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Zack Morris|Zack]] ([[Mark-Paul Gosselaar]]) asks [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Kelly Kapowski|Kelly]] ([[Tiffani Thiessen]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090924191747/http://www.thiessenpictures.com/index.php?cat=17|title=SEASONS 1 + 2 SCREENCAPS|last= |first= |date=December 17, 2006 |website=Tiffani Thiessen Photo Gallery|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>) to [[Courtship|go steady]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://abcswithrsp.blogspot.com/2011/03/classic-sbtb-from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=Classic SBTB: From Nurse To Worse|last= |first= |date=March 14, 2011|website=ABCs wth RSP|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kktybayside.blogspot.com/2011/01/from-nurse-to-worse.html|title=From Nurse to Worse|last=Weber|first=Korey|date=January 20, 2011|website=KKTY Bayside|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> with him, but while she is thinking it over, he falls<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sbtbreviewed.com/post/104670308015/sbtb-reviewed-episode-35-from-nurse-to-worse|title=SbtB Reviewed Episode 35: From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date= December 8, 2014|website=SbtB Reviewed|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> for a (supposedly) new student ([[Nancy Valen]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://podcasts.apple.com/au/podcast/nancy-valen-baywatch-heavenly-kid-nurse-jennifer-on/id1243077571?i=1000438680491|title=Nancy Valen (Baywatch, The Heavenly Kid, and \"Nurse Jennifer\" on Saved by the Bell)|last= |first= |date=May 17, 2019|website=Reliving My Youth|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://starsandcelebs.com/2010/09/eleven-people-might-not-know-saved-bell/|title=Eleven people you might not know were on 'Saved by the Bell'|last= |first= |date=September 27, 2010|website=Stars and Celebs|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://luminarypodcasts.com/listen/music-mania-286/saved-by-nostalgia-podcast/sbtb-from-nurse-to-worse-s2-e13/021d54f4-edbb-45a3-935a-4f2b4d78f7d1?country=US|title=SBTB- From Nurse to Worse (S2 E13)|last= |first= |date=July 5, 2019|website=SAVED BY NOSTALGIA PODCAST|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>), only to discover that she is actually the new school nurse.<ref>{{YouTube|title=45 - Saved By The Bell - S3E16 - From Nurse to Worse|id=lH96JoWcuMM}}</ref> Meanwhile, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#A.C. Slater|Slater]] ([[Mario Lopez]]) is afraid of getting his [[Influenza vaccine|flu shot]].\n\n==Plot==\nZack and Kelly arrive back at Kelly's house<ref>{{cite web |url=http://netchic.tripod.com/fromnursetoworse.html|title=SBTB - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date= |website=netchic.tripod.com|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> after their date to the movie ''[[Ernest Goes to Jail]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://savedbythebellblog.wordpress.com/2014/01/08/nurse-wretched/|title=Nurse Wretched|last= |first= |date=January 8, 2014|website=The Saved by the Bell Blog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> While at the front porch<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-k7DgJD5ey/|title=sbtbanniversary WEDNESDAY, APRIL 4, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 4, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>, Zack first ask Kelly that he wants to go steady with her before being interrupted by the voice Kelly's meddling little brother Kyle (Mark Neal) from upstairs. Kelly tells Zack that going steady is a big decision that she has to sleep on. The next day at Bayside, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Samuel \"Screech\" Powers|Screech]] ([[Dustin Diamond]]), [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Lisa Turtle|Lisa]], Jessie and Slater are discussing the upcoming school physical with Nurse Butcher (Justine Lenore<ref>{{cite web |url=http://epicsavedbythebell.blogspot.com/2014/02/sbtb-0216-from-nurse-to-worse.html |title=SBTB 02.16. - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first=|date=February 21, 2014|website=Epic Saved by the Bell|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gKLTsjkUz/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>). While Screech prepares by [[Exercise|exercising]] in the hallway, Jessie ([[Elizabeth Berkley]]) is emphatic that she's already in perfect health. Slater, meanwhile confesses that he doesn't like the annual physical, but won't further elaborate. Zack soon walks in and tells the gang about his intent on asking Kelly to go steady with him. The news is so hot, that Lisa ([[Lark Voorhies]]) plans to [[Gossip|spread it]] all around school.\n\nAs students clear out upon the ringing of the [[school bell]], Zack approached by a beautiful<ref>{{cite web |url=https://goat.com.au/saved-by-the-bell/30-years-on-zack-morris-is-still-the-most-problematic-character-in-saved-by-the-bell/|title=30 Years On, Zack Morris Is Still The Most Problematic Character In Saved By The Bell|last=Pan|first=Alexander|date=August 21, 2019|website=Goat|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> young woman named Jennifer<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/omarvillegas/a-definitive-ranking-of-guest-characters-on-saved-by-the-bel|title=A Definitive Ranking Of Guest Characters On \"Saved By The Bell\"|last=Villegas|first=Omar|date=October 17, 2014|website=Buzzfeed|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ([[Nancy Valen]]) who asks him for directions to the nurse's office. Zack is suddenly so [[Love at first sight|enamored]] by being in the woman's presence, that he is left literally [[Aphasia|speechless]]. Next in [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Mrs. Simpson|Miss Simpson's]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://the-talk.freeforums.net/thread/5538/saved-bell-episode-reviews-thread?page=27|title=SBTB 02.16. - From Nurse to Worse|last= |first= |date=December 29, 2014|website=Saved By The Bell Episode Reviews Thread|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> (Pamela Kosh<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gKh68jHQ9/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>) classroom, she informs her students about the [[Poetry|poems]] that they were supposed to write for [[English studies|English]] class. Right after Screech and Lisa read their respective poems, [[List of Saved by the Bell characters#Mr. Belding|Mr. Belding]] ([[Dennis Haskins]]) addresses the students on the [[intercom]] to remind them of the annual [[Physical examination|physicals]] and flu shots. When Belding himself volunteers for a shot<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-qWd17DHVb/|title=sbtbanniversary FRIDAY, APRIL 6, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 6, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>, he is overheard shrieking in pain, much to the discomfort of Slater. Finally when it's Kelly's turn to read her romantically themed poem, Zack imagines his new found [[Infatuation|crush]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://jumpedthesnark.com/2011/02/21/gratuitous-search-term-bait-of-the-day-hello-nurse/|title=Gratuitous Search Term Bait of the Day: Hellooooo Nurse|last= |first= |date=February 21, 2011|website=Jumped The Shark|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Jennifer addressing it towards him. Soon, Mr. Belding comes back on the intercom to tell Jessie and Zack to report to the nurse's office<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-k6-9eDRWq/|title=sbtbanniversary WEDNESDAY, APRIL 4, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 4, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>.\n\nWhile taking an [[eye examination]], Nurse Butcher tells Jessie that she's afraid that she might need glasses. After Butcher and Jessie leave, Jennifer walks in, now wearing her white [[White coat|medical coat]] and [[nurse uniform]]. To Zack's surprise, Jennifer tells him that she will be taking over from Nurse Butcher full-time the following month. Meanwhile, Kelly and Screech are in the hallway waiting for the end of Zack's physical. Kelly soon lets Screech in on her intent on saying yes<ref>{{cite web |url=https://guff.com/moments-that-prove-saved-by-the-bells-zack-morris-was-a-homicidal-maniac|title=Moments That Prove Saved by the Bell's Zack Morris Was a Homicidal Maniac|last=Porter |first=Joseph|date= |website=Guff|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to going steady with Zack. But as soon as Kelly sees Zack return from the nurse's office, he is completely oblivious to Kelly's feelings at the moment. Meanwhile, at The Max, Slater is trying to persuade Lisa or Jessie to [[Signature forgery|forge]] his mother's signature to get out of having to take the required flu shot at Bayside. Afterwards, an upset Kelly walks in and addresses to Lisa and Jessie her concerns about Zack not wanting to go out with her anymore. Jessie tries to calm Kelly's fears by telling her that she'll personally talk to Zack about the matter.\n\nIn Zack's bedroom, he is practicing [[flirting]] with Jennifer while in front of a mirror and wearing a [[Suit|suit]] and [[Necktie|tie]]. Soon, Jessie arrives via the open window and begins to inquire Zack about whether or not he's backing out on asking Kelly to go steady with him. Zack immediately confesses to Jessie about being in love<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/11/ranking-saved-by-the-bells-zack-morris-love-interests/|title=Ranking Saved By The Bell\u2019s Zack Morris\u2019 Love Interests|last=Fee|first=Rob |date=November 13, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> with Jennifer, the new school nurse.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thefederalist.com/2014/09/12/yo-slate-get-saved-by-the-bell-right/|title=Yo, Slate, Get \u2018Saved By The Bell\u2019 Right|last=Payne|first=Daniel|date=September 12, 2014|website=The Federalist|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> When a disgusted Jessie asks Zack if he somehow plans on dating Kelly and Jennifer at the same time, Zack begins to [[Sexual fantasy|fantasize]] about being a surgeon with Jennifer and Kelly<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-ngDqjjQ_v/|title=sbtbanniversary THURSDAY, APRIL 5, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 5, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/from-nurse-to-worse-episode-16-air-date-pictured-nancy-news-photo/141349256|title=SAVED BY THE BELL -- \"From Nurse to Worse\" Episode 16 -- Air Date 12/15/1990 -- Pictured: (l-r) Nancy Valen as Jennifer, Mark-Paul Gosselaar as Zack Morris, Tiffani Thiessen as Kelly Kapowski -- Photo by: Gary Null/NBCU Photo Bank|last= |first= |date= |website=Getty Images|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> as his nursing assistants. Although Jessie notes to Zack about how upset Kelly is going to be, Zack reminds Jessie that she promised not to tell anybody. While back in Miss Simpson's classroom, Zack feigns illness as a means of going back to the nurse's office to see Jennifer. Mr. Belding then walks in to tell Slater to report to his physical. In the nurse's office, Zack tells Jennifer that his head is [[Fever|feeling hot]] despite it feeling cool when Jennifer touches it. Shortly after Jennifer leaves the room to get her [[Medical thermometer|thermometer]] to take Zack's temperature, Slater walks in for his dreaded flu shot. But with the curtain drawn forward, Zack mistakenly believes that Slater is Jennifer. It is there that Zack inadvertently confesses to Slater his true feelings about Jennifer. Slater proceeds to [[blackmail]] Zack into another flu shot so that he won't tell Kelly or anybody else about his feelings for Jennifer.\n\nAt The Max, Zack desperately asks Screech if he knows anybody who could take Kelly's mind off him for a while so that he can pursue<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/10/the-30-greatest-episodes-of-saved-by-the-bell/|title=The 30 Greatest Episodes Of Saved By The Bell|last=Fee|first=Rob|date=October 28, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Jennifer. Screech then tells Zack about a new kid at school named Melvin Nerdly, who is a substitute on is [[Chess club|chess team]]. Shortly thereafter, Kelly walks in and is told by Zack that they should date other people for the time being. When Jessie, Slater and Lisa see Kelly suddenly leave in a huff, Lisa wonders what is troubling Kelly. Lisa though is immediately able to decipher Jessie and Slater's [[Cant (language)#Argot|secret language]] regarding the promise that they made to Zack about not telling anybody about his infatuation with Jennifer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.funnyordie.com/zack-morris-is-trash/2018/10/12/17965460/zack-morris-is-trash-dumped-girlfriend-school-nurse-saved-by-the-bell|title=The Time Zack Morris Dumped His Girlfriend To Harass The School Nurse|last=Driscoll|first=Dashiell|date=October 12, 2018|website=Funny or Die|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> So Lisa then, leads the way in telling Jennifer about Zack's neglect of Kelly. Jennifer when informed of this tells Jessie, Slater and Lisa to leave everything to her as she has had plenty of experience dealing with \"sick people\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldation.com/stories/ever-happened-women-saved-bell/|title=What ever happened to the women of Saved by the Bell?|last=Levis|first=Jamie|date=February 16, 2020|website=Worldnation|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Meanwhile, Jessie is emphatic that she didn't fail her initial eye exam under Nurse Butcher. Jennifer tells Jessie that the reason why she's retiring is due to her own failing [[Visual perception|eyesight]] and thus, Jessie doesn't need glasses after-all.\n\nThe next day, Zack enters the nurse's office upon Jennifer's request. When Zack sees Jennifer, she dressed decidedly more provocatively than her usual white nurse uniform: A purple [[T-shirt]], black [[miniskirt|tube miniskirt]], [[pantyhose]], a black [[Western wear|western]] [[Belt (clothing)|waist belt]], [[Shoulder pads (fashion)|shoulder pads]], [[Earring#Hoop earrings|hoop earrings]] and [[Court shoe|black pumps]]. Shortly thereafter, Jennifer locks the door, and while complaining about the warmth in the room, [[Seduction|sensually]] takes off her white coat, and takes out the [[Hair stick|stick]] that was holding her hair in a [[Bun (hairstyle)|bun]].<ref>{{YouTube|title=Nancy Valen lets her hair down. American actress takes stick out of her hair to drop bun. Beautiful|id=1BbRBsOCsjY}}</ref> Zack then nervously listens while Jennifer tells him about how she can't stop thinking about him<ref>{{cite web |url=https://postgradproblems.com/power-ranking-every-saved-by-the-bell-character/|title=Power Ranking Every \"Saved By The Bell\" Character|last= |first=|date=November 2, 2015 |website=Post Grad Problems|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> and how he's sweet unlike her fictional husband. Zack proceeds to panic when Jennifer tells him that her \"husband\" is a [[Professional wrestling|professional wrestler]] with a violent [[Temperament|temper]]. When Zack attempts to leave, Jennifer immediately corners him and tells him about how they should not only run away together, but also get married and have lots of children. Zack then tries to tell Jennifer that he already has a girlfriend in Kelly and that one girl is all that he can handle. Before finally allowing him to leave, Jennifer grabs Zack by the collar and boldly asks him if he wants a girl or a woman.\n\nThat evening, Zack is back at Kelly's front porch, where he finds finds Kelly on a date with Melvin Nerdly. Not only does Melvin play [[Chess|chess]], but [[List of multi-sport athletes|also]] [[American football|football]] and [[Ice hockey|hockey]] while also [[Model (person)|modeling]] a little. Zack tries to tell<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kiwireport.com/cast-saved-bell-now/|title=The cast of Saved by the Bell: then & now|last=Stevens|first=Stephanie|date=April 23, 2017|website=Kiwi Report|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Kelly that he really does want to go out with her and nobody else only to be immediately shut down by her. As Zack pleads to Kelly to take him back, Kyle upstairs warns Zack that he should leave or he'll be sorry. When Zack tells Kyle to mind his own business, Kyle retaliates by dumping a bucket a water on top of Zack's head.\n\n==Production==\nBefore Nancy Valen<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-imU58jPjv/|title=sbtbanniversary TUESDAY, APRIL 3, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 3, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=Splat From The Past #16- Nancy Valen|id=xBsQaSofv8M}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://open.spotify.com/episode/5myq4jJssbuUjPVI5e5Wym?si=YUDHMCalRMWbNlSc4hLn6A|title=TV Guidance Counselor Episode 382: Nancy Valen|last=Reid |first=Ken|date= |website=TV Guidance Counselor Podcast|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> was cast as Nurse Jennifer,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ebaumsworld.com/pictures/13-things-you-didnt-know-about-saved-by-the-bell/84305926/|title=13 Things You Didn't Know About Saved By The Bell|last= |first= |date=September 30, 2014|website=eBaum's World|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> supermodel [[Kathy Ireland]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-ilUUmDdut/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 3, 2020 |website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-gJQPtDlXF/|title=sbtbanniversary MONDAY, APRIL 2, 1990|last= |first= |date=April 2, 2020|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> was going to play<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tvovermind.com/10-things-didnt-know-saved-by-the-bell/|title=10 Things You Didn\u2019t Know About \u2018Saved by the Bell\u2019|last=Gerstenberger|first=Tim|date= |website=TV Overmind|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> the part. Ireland was however ultimately fired<ref>{{cite book |last=Ireland|first=Kathy|author-link= |date= |title=Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons That Will Change Your Life|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sphMwR7I6dwC&pg=PT70&lpg=PT70&dq=kathy+ireland+nurse+saved+by+the+bell&source=bl&ots=6H-MLLQBvK&sig=ACfU3U0-CcBF4NRfjTltKnMqkdPh3f8neQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjGprnZhdHoAhUGeKwKHXsFBhEQ6AEwFHoECA8QKQ#v=onepage&q=kathy%20ireland%20nurse%20saved%20by%20the%20bell&f=false|location= |publisher= |page= |isbn=}}</ref> during rehearsals after a disappointing [[Read-through|table read]] and a similarly disappointing [[Rehearsal#Dress rehearsal|dress rehearsal]]. \u201cShe must have dazzled us in the office, because I hired her on the spot,\u201d recalled co-creator [[Peter Engel]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://blog.truffleshuffle.co.uk/2015/01/10-things-you-probably-didnt-know-about%E2%80%A6saved-by-the-bell/|title=10 Things You [Probably] Didn\u2019t Know About\u2026Saved by the Bell|last= |first= |date=January 17, 2015|website=Truffle Shuffle|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Engel soon called Ireland's manager<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/10-things-you-didnt-know-about-saved-by-the-bell|title=10 Things You Didn't Know About 'Saved by the Bell'|last= |first= |date=August 20, 2014|website=Fox News|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to inform him that she couldn't do the part.\n\nKathy Ireland would right in her book ''Powerful Inspirations: Eight Lessons That Will Change Your Life'' that upon reading the script, she thought that her part was a little silly and she really couldn't connect with her character. Ireland added that she started asking herself a lot of questions, which resulted in her losing her focus. When the director kept telling her to just read her lines and to flirt with the boy (Zack) in a fantasy scene, Ireland attested that she didn't feel comfortable coming on<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.angelfire.com/80s/superstar10/sbtb.html|title=Inconsistencies on Saved by the Bell|last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> to a teenager. Ireland proclaimed that she just wasn't good enough of an actress to be able to give the director something that would make him happy without compromising her beliefs.\n\nMeanwhile, Jennifer calls Zack \"Loverboy\" when she tells Jessie, Slater and Lisa about getting him in her nurse's office and letting him see a side of her that he has never seen before. One year prior, Nancy Valen appeared in the 1989 film ''[[Loverboy (1989 film)|Loverboy]]'' also as a woman named [[Jennifer (given name)|Jennifer]] (or Jenny in this case).\n\n==Reception==\nLarry Fitzmaurice of [[Vulture.com]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2015/11/every-episode-of-saved-by-the-bell-ranked.html|title=Every Episode of Saved by the Bell, Ranked From Worst to Best|last=Fitzmaurice|first=Larry|date=November 2, 2015|website=Vulture|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ranked \"From Nurse to Worse\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225061544/http://www.savedbythebellreviewed.com/2014/08/22/saved-by-the-bell-season-2-episode-16-from-nurse-to-worse/|title=Saved by the Bell Season 2, Episode 16: \"From Nurse to Worse\"|last= |first= |date=August 22, 2014|website=Saved by the Bell...Reviewed!|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> at #74 among the 81 episodes (discounting its prequel, ''[[Good Morning, Miss Bliss]]'', [[Clip show|clip-show]] episodes, and combining two-part episodes into one) produced. Meanwhile, Rob Fee of ''[[Thought Catalog]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://thoughtcatalog.com/rob-fee/2013/10/the-30-greatest-episodes-of-saved-by-the-bell/ |title=The 30 Greatest Episodes Of Saved By The Bell|last=Fee|first=Rob|date=October 28, 2013|website=Thought Catalog|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ranked \"From Nurse to Worse\" at #30 among the top 30 greatest ''Saved by the Bell'' episodes. [[Uproxx]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uproxx.com/tv/all-86-saved-by-the-bell-episodes-definitively-ranked-by-imdb-users/|title=All 86 \u2018Saved By The Bell\u2019 Episodes, Definitively Ranked! (By IMDb Users)|last=Cormier|first=Roger|date=August 18, 2014|website=Uproxx|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> complied a ranking of episodes by [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]] users and \"From Nurse to Worse\" received a score of 7.1 from 57 users (10), thus coming in #25 out of 86 episodes.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb episode|0695194|From Nurse to Worse}}\n* {{tv.com episode|from-nurse-to-worse-21737|From Nurse to Worse}}\n\n{{Saved by the Bell}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:From Nurse to Worse (Saved by the Bell)}}\n[[Category:1990 American television episodes]]\n[[Category:Fictional nurses]]\n[[Category:Saved by the Bell (season 2) episodes]]\n", "name_user": "BornonJune8", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/From_Nurse_to_Worse_(Saved_by_the_Bell)"}
{"title_page": "Alfie McCalmont", "text_new": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Alfie McCalmont\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Alfie John McCalmont<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/image/201920/general-news/efl-squad-numbering-06.09.2019.pdf |title=Notification of shirt numbers: Leeds United |publisher=English Football League |page=36 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|03|25|df=y}}<ref name=\"WF\">{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/alfie-mccalmont/ |title=Alfie McCalmont: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Thirsk]], England\n| height = 1.67m<ref name=\"WF\"/>\n| position = [[Midfielder|Central midfielder]]<br>[[Midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| clubnumber = 38\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132019\n| youthclubs1 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years1 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\n| nationalteam1 = [[Northern Ireland national under-17 football team|Northern Ireland U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam2 = [[Northern Ireland national under-19 football team|Northern Ireland U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 5\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|Northern Ireland U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 8\n| nationalgoals3 = 1\n| nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 13 August 2019\n}}\n'''Alfie John McCalmont''' (born 25 March 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and the [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] national side as a [[Midfielder|central midfielder]]. He plays mainly as a [[Midfielder|defensive midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Thirsk]], he attended [[Thirsk School and Sixth Form College]] and came through the youth academy at [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/international/who-is-alfie-mccalmont-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-leeds-teenager-who-this-summer-trained-with-northern-ireland-38160362.html|date=13 August 2019|accessdate=19 April 2020|publisher=Belfast Telegraph|title=Who is Alfie McCalmont? All you need to know about the Leeds teenager who this summer trained with Northern Ireland|first=Gareth|last=Hanna}}</ref> He signed a professional contract extension on 22 January 2019 keeping him at the club until the summer of 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishfa.com/news/2019/january/northern-ireland-u19-alfie-mccalmont-signs-new-deal-at-leeds-united|title=Alfie McCalmont puts pen to paper on new contract at Leeds|date=22 January 2019|website=Irish FA|language=en|access-date=13 August 2019}}</ref> During the 2018/19 season, he featured regularly for [[Carlos Corber\u00e1n]]'s [[Leeds United F.C. Reserves and Youth Team|Leeds United under 23s]] side<ref>{{cite news |url=https://tbrfootball.com/true-leader-leeds-under-23-captain-hugo-diaz-impresses-the-fans-once-again/ |title='True leader' \u2013 Leeds under-23 captain Hugo Diaz impresses the fans once again |publisher=The Boot Room |date=12 March 2019 |accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref> that won the [[Professional Development League|PDL Northern League]] 2018/19 league title; they then became the national [[Professional Development League]] Champions by beating [[Birmingham City]] in the final.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-latest/carlos-corberan-on-what-the-future-can-hold-for-leeds-united-s-pdl-champions-1-9754577|date=7 May 2019|accessdate=15 May 2019|publisher=YEP|title=Carlos Corberan on what the future can hold for Leeds United's PDL champions}}</ref>\n\nMcCalmont started the first pre-season friendly of the 2019/20 season against [[York City]] in a 5\u20130 win on 10 July<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/25151/report-york-city-leeds-united|title=REPORT: YORK CITY 0\u20135 LEEDS UNITED|date=10 July 2019|website=www.leedsunited.com|language=en|access-date=13 August 2019}}</ref> and was named in the 1st team travelling squad on 4 August in Leeds' opening day 3\u20131 [[EFL Championship]] victory against [[Bristol City]]; he was left out of the final 18, but was allocated the 38 shirt for the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/25272/updates-bristol-city-v-leeds-united|title=Bristol City 1 Leeds 3|last=|first=|date=4 August 2019|website=Leeds United|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe was given his first team debut by head coach [[Marcelo Bielsa]] on 13 August in the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]], coming on as a substitute for [[Jack Clarke (footballer, born 2000)|Jack Clarke]] in the 70th minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=Salford City 0 Leeds United 3 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49245438 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe made his first Leeds start on 27 August 2019 in Leeds' EFL Cup match against [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]], with Leeds losing on 4\u20135 on penalties after a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/leeds-vs-stoke/420144|date=27 August 2019|accessdate=27 August 2019|publisher=Sky Sports|title=Leeds Vs Stoke}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe has represented Northern Ireland at international level up to [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|U21]]s. He was called up to the senior [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] squad in 2019 for a summer training camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/international/who-is-alfie-mccalmont-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-leeds-teenager-training-with-northern-ireland-38160362.html|title=Who is Alfie McCalmont? All you need to know about the Leeds teenager training with Northern Ireland|website=Belfast Telegraph|date=29 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe made his senior debut for [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] on 5 September 2019 coming on for [[George Saville]] as a 60th minute substitute in a 1-0 win against [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/football/leeds-united/leeds-united-latest/leeds-united-product-alfie-mccalmont-makes-senior-international-debut-in-northern-ireland-victory-1-9978792|title=Leeds United product Alfie McCalmont makes senior international debut in Northern Ireland victory|website=YEP|date=5 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nMcCalmont has also stated his eligibility for [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].{{fact|date=December 2019}}\n\n==Style of play==\nMcCalmont plays as a deep lying [[Midfielder|central midfielder]]. He plays mainly as a playmaking [[Midfielder|defensive midfielder]], known for his passing and ability on the ball, dictating the play.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/international/who-is-alfie-mccalmont-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-leeds-teenager-training-with-northern-ireland-38160362.html|title=Who is Alfie McCalmont? All you need to know about the Leeds teenager training with Northern Ireland|website=Belfast Telegraph|date=29 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nBelfast Live said McCalmont has \"excellent technique, is tenacious in the tackle and has an eye for a pass\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/who-alfie-mccalmont-meet-leeds-16345302|title=Who is Alfie McCalmont? Meet the Leeds prospect who trained with Northern Ireland this week |website=Belfast Live|date=29 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|27 August 2019}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Club\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! colspan=\"3\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |[[FA Cup]]\n! colspan=\"2\" |[[Football League Cup|League Cup]]\n! colspan=\"2\" |Other\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Division\n! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals !! Apps !! Goals\n|-\n|[[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Leeds United F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|124218|2019|accessdate=16 December 2019}}</ref>||[[Football League Championship|Championship]]\n | 0 || 0 || 0 || 0 || 2 || 0 || 0 || 0\n | 2 || 0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Total\n! 0 !! 0 !! 0 !! 0 !! 2 !! 0 !! 0 !! 0 !! 2 !! 0\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Leeds United F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McCalmont, Alfie}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Thirsk]]\n[[Category:Association footballers from Northern Ireland]]\n[[Category:Northern Ireland youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:English people of Northern Ireland descent]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Alfie McCalmont\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Alfie John McCalmont<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.efl.com/siteassets/image/201920/general-news/efl-squad-numbering-06.09.2019.pdf |title=Notification of shirt numbers: Leeds United |publisher=English Football League |page=36 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|2000|03|25|df=y}}<ref name=\"WF\">{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/alfie-mccalmont/ |title=Alfie McCalmont: Profile |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Thirsk]], England\n| height = 1.67m<ref name=\"WF\"/>\n| position = [[Midfielder|Central midfielder]]<br>[[Midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| clubnumber = 38\n| youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132019\n| youthclubs1 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years1 = 2019\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\n| nationalteam1 = [[Northern Ireland national under-17 football team|Northern Ireland U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2017\u20132018\n| nationalteam2 = [[Northern Ireland national under-19 football team|Northern Ireland U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 5\n| nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|Northern Ireland U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 5\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2019\u2013\n| nationalteam4 = [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 13 August 2019\n}}\n'''Alfie John McCalmont''' (born 25 March 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] and the [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] national side as a [[Midfielder|central midfielder]]. He plays mainly as a [[Midfielder|defensive midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Thirsk]], he attended [[Thirsk School and Sixth Form College]] and came through the youth academy at [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{citew