1/report-york-city-leeds-united|title=REPORT: YORK CITY 0\u20135 LEEDS UNITED|date=10 July 2019|website=www.leedsunited.com|language=en|access-date=13 August 2019}}</ref> and was named in the 1st team travelling squad on 4 August in Leeds' opening day 3\u20131 [[EFL Championship]] victory against [[Bristol City]]; he was left out of the final 18, but was allocated the 38 shirt for the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.leedsunited.com/news/team-news/25272/updates-bristol-city-v-leeds-united|title=Bristol City 1 Leeds 3|last=|first=|date=4 August 2019|website=Leeds United|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe was given his first team debut by head coach [[Marcelo Bielsa]] on 13 August in the [[EFL Cup]] against [[Salford City F.C.|Salford City]], coming on as a substitute for [[Jack Clarke (footballer, born 2000)|Jack Clarke]] in the 70th minute.<ref>{{cite web |title=Salford City 0 Leeds United 3 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49245438 |website=BBC Sport |accessdate=13 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe made his first Leeds start on 27 August 2019 in Leeds' EFL Cup match against [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]], with Leeds losing on 4\u20135 on penalties after a 2\u20132 draw.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/leeds-vs-stoke/420144|date=27 August 2019|accessdate=27 August 2019|publisher=Sky Sports|title=Leeds Vs Stoke}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nHe has represented Northern Ireland at international level up to [[Northern Ireland national under-21 football team|U21]]s. He was called up to the senior [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]] squad in 2019 for a summer training camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/international/who-is-alfie-mccalmont-all-you-need-to-know-about-the-leeds-teenager-training-with-northern-ireland-38160362.html|title=Who is Alfie McCalmont? All you need to know about the Leeds teenager training with Northern Ireland|website=B