{"title_page": "1971 New Year Honours", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2016}}\nThe '''New Year Honours 1971''' were appointments in many of the [[Commonwealth realm]]s of Queen [[Elizabeth II]] to [[Orders and decorations of the Commonwealth realms|various orders and honours]] to reward and highlight good works by citizens of those countries. They were announced in supplements to the ''[[London Gazette]]'' of 31 December 1970 to celebrate the year passed and mark the beginning of 1971.<ref>United Kingdom list: {{London Gazette |issue=45262 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=1\u201332   |supp=y}}</ref><ref name=\"Australia\">Australia list: {{London Gazette |issue=45263 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=33\u201338  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>New Zealand list: {{London Gazette |issue=45264 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=39\u201342  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Sierra Leone list: {{London Gazette |issue=45265 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=43\u201344  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Barbados list: {{London Gazette |issue=45266 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=45\u201346  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Mauritius list: {{London Gazette |issue=45267 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=47\u201348  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Fiji list: {{London Gazette |issue=45268 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=49\u201350  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref>\n\nAt this time honours for Australians were awarded both in the United Kingdom honours, on the advice of the premiers of Australian states, and also in a separate Australia honours list.<ref name=\"Australia\"/>\n\nThe recipients of honours are displayed here as they were styled before their new honour, and arranged by honour, with classes (Knight, Knight Grand Cross, ''etc.'') and then divisions (Military, Civil, ''etc.'') as appropriate.\n\n==United Kingdom and Commonwealth==\n\n===Baron===\n;[[Life Peer]]\n* Sir [[Charles Maclean, Baron Maclean|Charles Hector Fitzroy Maclean]], {{post-nominals|list=Bt., KT, KBE}}, [[Chief Scout]] of the Commonwealth.\n* The Right Honourable Sir [[Jocelyn Edward Salis Simon]], President of the Probate, Divorce and Admiralty Division of the [[High Court of Justice]].\n* Sir [[Miles Thomas|(William) Miles Webster Thomas]], {{post-nominals|list=DFC}}, President and lately Chairman, [[National Savings Committee]].\n\n===Privy Counsellor===\n* The Honourable Sir [[Cyril Walsh|Cyril Ambrose Walsh]], {{post-nominals|list=KBE}}, a [[List of Justices of the High Court of Australia|Justice of the High Court of Australia]].\n\n===Knight Bachelor===\n* [[William Melville Arnott]], {{post-nominals|list=TD, FRCP (Ed.)}}, William Withering Professor of Medicine, [[University of Birmingham]].\n* Maurice Alfred Lister Banks. For services to Patent Law.\n* David Haven Barran, Chairman, [[Shell Transport and Trading]] Co. Ltd.\n* [[Raymond Brookes, Baron Brookes|Raymond Percival Brookes]], Chairman and Chief Executive, [[Guest Keen and Nettlefolds]] Ltd. For services to Export.\n* [[Leslie Cannon]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, General President, [[Electrical, Electronic, Telecommunications and Plumbing Union]]. (Died 9 December 1970 after the Honour was approved.)\n* [[Fred Catherwood|Henry Frederick Ross Catherwood]], Director-General, [[National Economic Development Office]].\n* Henry Chisholm, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Chairman, Corby Development Corporation.\n* [[Alan Howard Cottrell]], Deputy Chief Scientific Adviser to the Government.\n* Cyril Thomas Cripps, {{post-nominals|list=MBE}}. For public and charitable services.\n* Professor [[Frederick Sydney Dainton]]. For services to Science and Higher Education.\n* [[George Edward Raven Deacon]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Director, [[National Oceanography Centre|National Institute of Oceanography]].\n* Gerald Alfred Glover. For political and public services.\n* Francis Frederick Griffin, Alderman, [[Birmingham City Council]].\n* Adrian Lincoln Hallinan, {{post-nominals|list=DL}}. For local government and public services in Cardiff.\n* [[John Wyndham Pope-Hennessy]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}. For services to Fine Art.\n* [[Bryan Hopkin|William Aylsham Bryan Hopkin]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Deputy Chief Economic Adviser, [[HM Treasury]].\n* Cyril Hugh Kleinwort, Chairman, Committee on Invisible Exports.\n* [[Donald Liddle|Donald Ross Liddle]], {{post-nominals|list=DL}}, [[Lord Provost of Glasgow|Lord Provost of the City of Glasgow]].\n* [[Wylie McKissock]], {{post-nominals|list=OBE, MS, FRCS}}, Neurological Surgeon.\n* Henry Stenhouse Mance, Chairman of [[Lloyd's of London|Lloyd's]].\n* [[Frank Shaw Marshall]], Alderman, [[Leeds City Council]].\n* Stirrat Andrew William Johnson-Marshall, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Senior Partner, [[Robert Matthew Johnson Marshall]] and Partners.\n* [[Douglas Osmond]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE, QPM}}, Chief Constable, [[Hampshire Constabulary]].\n* [[Denys Lionel Page]], [[Regius Professor of Greek (Cambridge)|Regius Professor of Greek, University of Cambridge]].\n* The Right Honourable [[Robert Wilson Porter]], {{post-nominals|list=QC, MP}}, [[Minister of Home Affairs (Northern Ireland)|Minister of Home Affairs, Government of Northern Ireland]], 1969-70.\n* Humphrey Povah Treverbian Prideaux, {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}, Chairman, [[Navy, Army and Air Force Institutes]].\n* William Clark Ramsay, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}. For services to Rugby Football.\n* [[Alex Ross (rower)|Alexander Ross]], lately Chairman, East European Trade Council. For services to Export.\n* The Honourable [[Marcus Joseph Sieff]], {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}, Joint Managing Director, [[Marks & Spencer]] Ltd. For services to Export.\n\n;Diplomatic Service and Overseas List\n* [[William Gordon Bryce]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE, QC}}, [[Chief Justice of the Bahamas|Chief Justice, Bahama Islands]].\n* The Honourable Mr. Justice William Algernon Holwell Duffus, President, Court of Appeal for East Africa.\n* The Honourable [[Kenneth Fung|Kenneth Fung Ping-fan]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}. For public and social services in Hong Kong.\n* [[Rupert Godfrey John]], [[Governor of Saint Vincent]].\n\n;;State of New South Wales\n* The Honourable [[Asher Joel|Asher Alexander Joel]], {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}. For services to the community.\n* Matthew John O'Neill, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}. For services to commerce and charity.\n* Raymond Edgar Purves, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}. For services to the community.\n\n;;State of Victoria\n* Charles Roger Darvall, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, of Toorak. For public service.\n* Professor Sydney Lance Townsend, {{post-nominals|list=VRD, MD, FRCS}}, of Hawthorn East. Professor of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, [[University of Melbourne]].\n\n;;State of Queensland\n* The Honourable [[Harold Richter]], of Brisbane. For outstanding public services.\n\n;;State of Western Australia\n* [[Norman Brearley]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE, DSO, MC, AFC}}. For services to aviation.\n* Reginald Fielding Rushton, of Perth. For outstanding service to the community.\n\n;;State of Tasmania\n* The Honourable [[Alfred John White]], [[Agent-General]] for Tasmania in London.\n\n===Order of the Bath===\n\n====Knight Grand Cross of the Order of the Bath (GCB)====\n;Military Division\n* Admiral Sir [[Michael Pollock|Michael Patrick Pollock]], {{post-nominals|list=KCB, MVO, DSC}}.\n* General Sir [[Desmond Fitzpatrick]], {{post-nominals|list=KCB, DSO, MBE, MC, ADC (Gen.)}}, (53670) late [[Royal Armoured Corps]], Deputy Colonel The [[Blues and Royals]].\n* Air Chief Marshal Sir [[Denis Spotswood]], {{post-nominals|list=KCB, CBE, DSO, DFC, ADC}}, [[Royal Air Force]].\n\n;Civil Division\n* Sir [[George Godber|George Edward Godber]], {{post-nominals|list=KCB, DM, FRCP}}, [[Chief Medical Officer (United Kingdom)|Chief Medical Officer]], [[Department of Health and Social Security]], [[Department of Education and Science (UK)|Department of Education and Science]], and [[Home Office]].\n\n====Knight Commander of the Order of the Bath (KCB)====\n;Military Division\n* Admiral [[Edward Ashmore|Edward Beckwith Ashmore]], {{post-nominals|list=CB, DSC}}.\n* Vice-Admiral [[Andrew Lewis (Royal Navy officer)|Andrew Mackenzie Lewis]], {{post-nominals|list=CB}}.\n* Lieutenant-General [[William Godfrey Fothergill Jackson]], {{post-nominals|list=OBE, MC}}, (73056), late [[Corps of Royal Engineers]].\n* Lieutenant-General [[Richard Ward (British Army officer)|Richard Erskine Ward]], {{post-nominals|list=CB, DSO, MC}}, (73199), late Royal Armoured Corps, [[Colonel Commandant]] [[Royal Tank Regiment]].\n* Air Marshal [[Derek Hodgkinson|William Derek Hodgkinson]], {{post-nominals|list=CB, CBE, DFC, AFC}}, Royal Air Force.\n* Air Marshal [[Harold Brownlow Martin]], {{post-nominals|list=CB, DSO, DFC, AFC}}, Royal Air Force.\n\n;Civil Division\n* William Dennis Pile, {{post-nominals|list=CB, MBE}}, [[Permanent Under-Secretary of State]], [[Department of Education and Science (UK)|Department of Education and Science]].\n\n====Companion of the Order of the Bath (CB)====\n;Military Division\n;;Royal Navy\n* Rear Admiral Charles Courtney Anderson.\n* Rear Admiral [[Derrick Kent|Derrick George Kent]].\n* Rear Admiral [[Nigel Malim|Nigel Hugh Malim]], {{post-nominals|list=MVO}}.\n* Rear Admiral Douglas Granger Parker, {{post-nominals|list=DSO, DSC, AFC}}.\n\n;;Army\n* Major-General Denis Arthur Beckett, {{post-nominals|list=DSO, OBE}}, (113508), late Infantry.\n* Major-General John Cain Cowley (141546), [[Royal Army Pay Corps]].\n* Brigadier Barbara Masson Gordon, {{post-nominals|list=RRC, QHNS}}, (206176), [[Queen Alexandra's Royal Army Nursing Corps]].\n* Major-General [[Frank Douglas King]], {{post-nominals|list=MBE}}, (138204), late Infantry.\n* Major-General [[David Lloyd Owen|David Lanyon Lloyd Owen]], {{post-nominals|list=DSO, OBE, MC}}, (74596), late Infantry.\n* Major-General Alexander Young (174093), late [[Royal Army Ordnance Corps]].\n\n;;Royal Air Force\n* Air Vice-Marshal [[Neil Cameron, Baron Cameron of Balhousie|Neil Cameron]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE, DSO, DFC}}.\n* Air Vice-Marshal [[Nigel Maynard|Nigel Martin Maynard]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE, DFC, AFC}}.\n* Air Vice-Marshal Leslie Howard Moulton, {{post-nominals|list=DFC}}.\n* Air Commodore Charles Duncan Alfred Browne, {{post-nominals|list=DFC}}.\n \n;Civil Division\n* [[Frederick Atkinson|Frederick John Atkinson]], Chief Economic Adviser, [[Department of Trade and Industry (United Kingdom)|Department of Trade and Industry]].\n* Clifford Henry Baylis, Controller, [[HM Stationery Office]].\n* Basil Edmund Bellamy, Under-Secretary, [[Department of Trade and Industry (United Kingdom)|Department of Trade and Industry]].\n* Norman Coles, Deputy Chief Adviser (Research and Studies), [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]].\n* Peter Richmond Cox, [[Government Actuary's Department|Deputy Government Actuary]].\n* Herbert Clyde Fitzer, {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}, Director of Engineering (Ships) and Head of the Royal Naval Engineering Service, Ministry of Defence.\n* Leonard Ralph Fletcher, Secretary, [[University Grants Committee (UK)|University Grants Committee]].\n* Thomas Charles Green, [[Charity Commission for England and Wales|Chief Charity Commissioner]].\n* Eric William Charles Lewis, Controller of Death Duties, [[Board of Inland Revenue]].\n* [[Jean Nunn|Jean Josephine Nunn]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, lately Deputy Secretary, [[Cabinet Office]].\n* John Glendwr Owen, Under-Secretary, HM Treasury.\n* Ronald Walter Radford, {{post-nominals|list=MBE}}, Deputy Chairman, [[Board of Customs and Excise]].\n* Hume Boggis-Rolfe, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Deputy [[Clerk of the Crown in Chancery]] and Deputy Permanent Secretary to the Lord Chancellor.\n* Peter Eustace Thornton, Deputy Secretary, [[Cabinet Office]].\n* Henry Gabriel Ware, Deputy [[Treasury Solicitor]].\n* [[Henry Yellowlees]], {{post-nominals|list=MRCP, MRCS}}, Deputy Chief Medical Officer, Department of Health and Social Security.\n\n===Order of Saint Michael and Saint George===\n\n====Knight Grand Cross of the Order of St Michael and St George (GCMG)====\n* Sir [[Charles Hepburn Johnston]], {{post-nominals|list=KCMG}}, [[List of High Commissioners of the United Kingdom to Australia|British High Commissioner, Canberra]].\n\n====Knight Commander of the Order of St Michael and St George (KCMG)====\n* [[Peter Hayman (diplomat)|Peter Telford Hayman]], {{post-nominals|list=CMG, CVO, MBE}}, [[List of High Commissioners of the United Kingdom to Canada|British High Commissioner, Ottawa]].\n\n====Companion of the Order of St Michael and St George (CMG)====\n* Arthur Hugh Bunting, Professor of Agricultural Botany, [[University of Reading]]. For services to developing countries.\n* [[James Richard Cross]], lately Senior British Trade Commissioner, Montreal.\n* Stanley Mason Davies, Assistant Secretary, Department of Health and Social Security.\n* John Ivor McKinnon Rhodes, Minister, United Kingdom Mission to the United Nations.\n* Lilian Katherine Somerville, {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}, Director, Fine Arts Department, [[British Council]].\n\n;Diplomatic Service and Overseas List \n* [[Gillian Gerda Brown]], Counsellor and Head of Chancery, HM Embassy, Berne.\n* John Christopher Wyndowe Bushell, Minister and Deputy Commandant, British Military Government, Berlin.\n* Ronald Lawrie Huckstep, {{post-nominals|list=MD, FRCS}}, Honorary Surgeon-in-Charge, Round Table Polio Clinic, Kampala.\n* Kenneth James Knaggs, {{post-nominals|list=OBE}}, formerly Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Defence, Zambia.\n* [[Daphne Park|Daphne Margaret Sybil Desiree Park]], HM Consul-General, Hanoi.\n* James Grant Purves, HM Consul-General, Hamburg.\n* Alastair Todd, Defence Secretary, Hong Kong.\n* [[Peter Tripp (diplomat)|John Peter Tripp]], [[List of ambassadors of the United Kingdom to Libya|HM Ambassador, Tripoli]].\n\n;;State of New South Wales\n* [[Charles Aubrey Hardwick]], {{post-nominals