or public services.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Honours Lists}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:New Year Honours 1971}}\n[[Category:New Year Honours]]\n[[Category:1971 in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:1971 in Australia]]\n[[Category:1971 in Sierra Leone]]\n[[Category:1971 in Barbados]]\n[[Category:1970s in Mauritius]]\n[[Category:1971 in Fiji]]\n[[Category:1971 awards]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2016}}\nThe '''New Year Honours 1971''' were appointments in many of the [[Commonwealth realm]]s of Queen [[Elizabeth II]] to [[Orders and decorations of the Commonwealth realms|various orders and honours]] to reward and highlight good works by citizens of those countries. They were announced in supplements to the ''[[London Gazette]]'' of 31 December 1970 to celebrate the year passed and mark the beginning of 1971.<ref>United Kingdom list: {{London Gazette |issue=45262 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=1\u201332   |supp=y}}</ref><ref name=\"Australia\">Australia list: {{London Gazette |issue=45263 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=33\u201338  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>New Zealand list: {{London Gazette |issue=45264 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=39\u201342  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Sierra Leone list: {{London Gazette |issue=45265 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=43\u201344  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Barbados list: {{London Gazette |issue=45266 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=45\u201346  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Mauritius list: {{London Gazette |issue=45267 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=47\u201348  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref><ref>Fiji list: {{London Gazette |issue=45268 |date=31 December 1970 |pages=49\u201350  |supp=y |nolink=yes}}</ref>\n\nAt this time honours for Australians were awarded both in the United Kingdom honours, on the advice of the premiers of Australian states, and also in a separate Australia honours list.<ref name=\"Australia\"/>\n\nThe recipients of honours are displayed here as they were styled before their new honour, and arranged by honour, with classes (Knight, Knight Grand Cross, ''etc.'') and then divisions (Military, Civil, ''etc.'') as appropriate.\n\n==United Kingdom and Commonwealth==\n\n===Baron===\n;[[Life Peer]]\n* Sir [[Charles Maclean, Baron Maclean|Charles Hector Fitzroy Maclean]], {{post-nominals|list=Bt., KT, KBE}}, [[Chief Scout]] of the Commonwealth.\n* The Right Honourable Sir [[Jocelyn Edward Salis Simon]], President of the Probate, Divorce and Admiralty Division of the [[High Court of Justice]].\n* Sir [[Miles Thomas|(William) Miles Webster Thomas]], {{post-nominals|list=DFC}}, President and lately Chairman, [[National Savings Committee]].\n\n===Privy Counsellor===\n* The Honourable Sir [[Cyril Walsh|Cyril Ambrose Walsh]], {{post-nominals|list=KBE}}, a [[List of Justices of the High Court of Australia|Justice of the High Court of Australia]].\n\n===Knight Bachelor===\n* [[William Melville Arnott]], {{post-nominals|list=TD, FRCP (Ed.)}}, William Withering Professor of Medicine, [[University of Birmingham]].\n* Maurice Alfred Lister Banks. For services to Patent Law.\n* David Haven Barran, Chairman, [[Shell Transport and Trading]] Co. Ltd.\n* [[Raymond Brookes, Baron Brookes|Raymond Percival Brookes]], Chairman and Chief Executive, [[Guest Keen and Nettlefolds]] Ltd. For services to Export.\n* [[Leslie Cannon]], {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, General President, [[Electrical, Electronic, Telecommunications and Plumbing Union]]. (Died 9 December 1970 after the Honour was approved.)\n* [[Fred Catherwood|Henry Frederick Ross Catherwood]], Director-General, [[National Economic Development Office]].\n* Henry Chisholm, {{post-nominals|list=CBE}}, Chairman, Corby Development Corporation.\n* [[Alan Howard Cottrell]], Deputy Chief Scientific Adviser to the Government.\n* Cyril Thomas Cripps, {{post-nominals|list=MBE}}. For public and charitable services.\n* Professor [[Frederick Sydney Dainton]]. For services to Science and Higher Educat